        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 4 at 4:02PM PDT by NWS Hanford CA</headline>
        <description>At 402 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northwest of Tioga Pass, or 10 miles south of Twin Lakes,
moving south at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tioga Pass and Glen Aulin High Sierra Camp.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
